editorialNotes.standard: Bursting with beats and energy, Toca Dance will make the whole family want to get up and groove. This incredibly cute game puts kids in charge of their own musical productionâ€”choosing dancers, costumes and techno tracks, and choreographing moves using simple swipes and taps. Once the performance starts, the real fun begins: you can fling items at the stage, set off pyrotechnics and other cool effects and even cheer (or boo) your squad. Seeing the payoffâ€”an awesome video you can shareâ€”will encourage players to jump right back in and start working on their next great show.

editorialNotes.short: Compose fun musical beats with amusing animals.

editorialNotes.standard: An utterly charming way to introduce young kids to music and animation, Loopimal is simple and powerful in a way that almost defies description. Kids arrange and rearrange tiles in sequences underneath a cute polar bear, octopus, and the like, triggering a series of musical tones mirrored by adorable dances from the animal gang. There are no goals and no consequencesâ€”just a safe place to learn, play, and laugh.

Nothing beats a kid-friendly game that keeps the whole family captivatedâ€”and Toca has us snipping, straightening, and styling to our heart's content. Once we've perfected our customer's silly new â€˜dos, we make sure to add some accessories, snap a pic, and share the hair.
